{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PRWERsVkhwRpdZuwpHLteN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me outline the key proposed changes and write the improvement plan.\n\nThe single failure is:\n- **\"Smażona zielona fasolka\"** → got empty string (undefined)\n\nRoot causes from the feedback:\n1. **Bilingual join contamination**: Multi-line joins like \"Smażona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" aren't suppressed by the bilingual filter (which only checks `startsWith`)\n2. **Structural bonus misallocation**: \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" gets structural bonus (+0.10) and ALL_CAPS bonus (+0.08) before bilingual detection removes it from `scoredForThreshold`, but these bonuses live in the `scored` array used by the fallback path\n\n\n3. **Diacritic-stripped section labels**: \"SKLADNIKI\" (without ą) doesn't match \"składniki\" in SECTION_LABELS\n\nI'm tracing through the algorithm with the actual input to see how these issues cascade—the multi-language lines, the garbled Korean text, and the long prose all interact to push the Polish ingredient name out of the results. I see the issue now—the bilingual filter is removing standalone translations but missing cases where the translation appears within a longer phrase. So \"Smażona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" survives because it starts with Polish text, even though it contains the English translation. This contaminated version gets a structural bonus during scoring, which inflates the threshold and causes the clean Polish-only title to fall below it. I need to extend the filter to catch translations anywhere in the candidate, not just at the start.\n\nI also need to prevent structural bonuses from being assigned to translation candidates in the first place, either by running bilingual detection earlier or stripping the bonus afterward. And for the section label matching, I should normalize diacritics using Unicode NFKD...\n\nNormalizing diacritics...\n\nLooking at the accuracy pattern across iterations, there's definitely a whack-a-mole dynamic happening, but iteration 16 is performing well at 10/11 cases. These targeted fixes shouldn't cascade into breaking other cases since they're addressing specific matching logic rather than the core ranking system.\n\nThe bilingual filter needs to be more aggressive—checking not just `startsWith` but also `endsWith` and `includes` to catch partial matches. For the structural bonus, I should only apply it when the heading itself is a translation rather than just any case with detected bilingual content.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":448,"cache_read_input_tokens":61558,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":448},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9e805fa1-f282-4af7-9433-5ad139358a2e","uuid":"138d255a-5829-40f4-af5b-2fadd5f5ce7d"}
