{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01F1LgG22Sq9Bp2Cuw2NC25F","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md`.\n\n**Three fixes, one primary:**\n\n1. **Primary — Extend bilingual suppression** (~5 lines): Change the `scoredForThreshold` filter from `startsWith` only to also check `endsWith` and `includes(\" \" + ...)`. This removes contaminated multi-line joins like \"Smażona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" that currently slip through because they start with Polish, not English.\n\n2. **Defense-in-depth — Reassign structural bonus** (~15 lines): After bilingual detection identifies \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" as a translation, strip its +0.10 structural bonus from the `scored` array. This prevents the fallback path and threshold calculation from being poisoned by the misallocated bonus.\n\n3. **Noise reduction — Diacritic-insensitive section labels** (~8 lines): Add Unicode NFKD normalization to `isSectionLabel` so \"SKLADNIKI\" matches \"składniki\". Secondary fix that removes noise from threshold calculation.\n\nFix 1 alone should resolve the failure. Fixes 2 and 3 harden the pipeline against related edge cases."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6304,"cache_read_input_tokens":62006,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6304},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9e805fa1-f282-4af7-9433-5ad139358a2e","uuid":"4666f241-1344-4a08-a26b-b00e56cdafa5"}
